<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n41036c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41036c">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41036c"> 36(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> the true wife</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">On a prosecution for bigamy, the general rule that the husband or wife of the accused cannot give evidence without the consent of the accused, does not apply; and <mark>the true husband or wife</mark> may be called to give evidence for the prosecution without such consent. <small> Maud I. Crofts, <a name="MICW" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#MICW"><cite title="source">Women under English Law</cite></a>, 1st ed. (1925) 32</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
